German carmaker Volkswagen says it will launch its new Polo model in South Africa in early 2022. Announced globally on Thursday (22 April), Volkswagen said that the new model will be available in three different configurations including a Life, Style and R-Line versions. Volkswagen added that the new models will feature technologies that have previously only been available in higher vehicle classes. This will include the predictive ACC (Adaptive Cruise Control) and Lane Assist â€“ which now comes as standard in every Polo, it said. <img class="size-full wp-image-485363 aligncenter" src="https://businesstech.co.za/news/wp-content/uploads/2021/04/Polo-2.jpg" alt="" width="1260" height="710" srcset="https://businesstech.co.za/news/wp-content/uploads/2021/04/Polo-2.jpg 1260w, https://businesstech.co.za/news/wp-content/uploads/2021/04/Polo-2-300x169.jpg 300w, https://businesstech.co.za/news/wp-content/uploads/2021/04/Polo-2-1024x577.jpg 1024w, https://businesstech.co.za/news/wp-content/uploads/2021/04/Polo-2-768x433.jpg 768w, https://businesstech.co.za/news/wp-content/uploads/2021/04/Polo-2-1200x676.jpg 1200w" sizes="(max-width: 709px) 85vw, (max-width: 909px) 67vw, (max-width: 1362px) 62vw, 840px" /> <img class="size-full wp-image-485365 aligncenter" src="https://businesstech.co.za/news/wp-content/uploads/2021/04/Polo-3.jpg" alt="" width="1260" height="710" srcset="https://businesstech.co.za/news/wp-content/uploads/2021/04/Polo-3.jpg 1260w, https://businesstech.co.za/news/wp-content/uploads/2021/04/Polo-3-300x169.jpg 300w, https://businesstech.co.za/news/wp-content/uploads/2021/04/Polo-3-1024x577.jpg 1024w, https://businesstech.co.za/news/wp-content/uploads/2021/04/Polo-3-768x433.jpg 768w, https://businesstech.co.za/news/wp-content/uploads/2021/04/Polo-3-1200x676.jpg 1200w" sizes="(max-width: 709px) 85vw, (max-width: 909px) 67vw, (max-width: 1362px) 62vw, 840px" /> <img class="size-full wp-image-485367 aligncenter" src="https://businesstech.co.za/news/wp-content/uploads